{
  "texts": [
    "Pound for pound, the comparative impact of CH4 is 28 times greater than CO2 over a 100-year period.Agriculture.",
    "Domestic livestock such as cattle, swine, sheep, and goats produce CH4 as part of their normal digestive process.",
    "Also, when animal manure is stored or managed in lagoons or holding tanks, CH4 is produced.",
    "Because humans raise these animals for food and other products, the emissions are considered human-related.Energy and Industry.",
    "Natural gas and petroleum systems are the second largest source of CH4 emissions."
  ]
}